author: WCAX News
title: Bennington women processed for DUI after reporting alleged assau
text:
BENNINGTON, Vt. - A woman who went to police to report one crime got in trouble for another Wednesday.
Vermont State Police say Loralie Osgood, 39, of Bennington, showed up at the Shaftsbury Barracks to report a possible assault.
Authorities say she appeared drunk. They processed her for DUI and say her blood alcohol content was roughly three times over the legal limit.
Police are still investigating the alleged assault.
